  "prompt": "Why can't I change my profile picture on Quora via my phone?",
  "response": "If you're having trouble changing your profile picture on Quora via your phone, there could be several reasons for this. Here are some common issues and solutions:\n\n1. **App Version**: Ensure that you have the latest version of the Quora app installed on your phone. Sometimes, bugs in older versions can cause issues.\n\n2. **Internet Connection**: Check if your internet connection is stable. A weak or unstable connection could prevent the upload from completing.\n\n3. **File Format and Size**: Ensure that the image you are trying to upload meets Quora's requirements regarding file format (JPEG, PNG, etc.) and size.\n\n4. **Permissions**: Make sure that the Quora app has permission to access your phone's storage or photo library.\n\n5. **Logout and Re-login**: Sometimes, logging out of your account and logging back in can resolve temporary glitches.\n\n6. **Clear Cache**: If you're using the app, try clearing the app cache. This can sometimes fix issues with the app's performance.\n\n7. **Try Using a Browser**: If you still can't change your profile picture through the app, try accessing Quora via a web browser on your phone.\n\nIf none of the above solutions work, you may want to reach out to Quora's support for further assistance.",
